<paragraph id="A00BF065FFAAFFDBAEC47ED2FC35468E" blockId="1.[151,1436,713,1243]" box="[151,898,713,739]" pageId="1" pageNumber="302">
<typeStatus id="7F0F4EC7FFAAFFDBAEC47ED2FF78468E" box="[151,207,713,739]" pageId="1" pageNumber="302">Type</typeStatus>
species: 
<taxonomicName id="67B48BE6FFAAFFDBAF667ED2FDC1468E" authority="Cushman" authorityName="Cushman" authorityYear="1922" box="[309,630,713,739]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Apophysius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bakeri">
<emphasis id="92C02C77FFAAFFDBAF667ED2FDB1468E" box="[309,518,713,739]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="302">Apophysius bakeri</emphasis>
Cushman
</taxonomicName>
by original description.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A00BF065FFAAFFDBAE947EF6FED1404A" blockId="1.[151,1436,713,1243]" pageId="1" pageNumber="302">
Diagnosis. 
<taxonomicName id="67B48BE6FFAAFFDBAF157EF6FE70476A" authorityName="Cushman" authorityYear="1922" box="[326,455,749,775]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Apophysius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="92C02C77FFAAFFDBAF157EF6FE70476A" box="[326,455,749,775]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="302">Apophysius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by numerous apomorphies. Head and mesosoma densely covered with long blond setae; apical margin of clypeus broadly convex, with two small projections at the center; upper mandibular tooth larger and much longer than lower tooth; occipital carina complete; mesoscutum with notauli indistinct; subtegular ridge sharp, laterally expanded in dorsal view; posterior edge of mesoscutum with suture before scutoscutellar groove; propodeum with four tubercles (apophyses) at intersections of lateral longitudinal carinae with anterior and posterior transverse carinae; tarsal claws conspicuously pectinate proximally; fore wing with vein 3 
<emphasis id="92C02C77FFAAFFDBAB3A7FB9FA2B47D6" box="[1385,1436,930,955]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="302">rs-m</emphasis>
present, almost parallel to 2 
<emphasis id="92C02C77FFAAFFDBAF9C7FDDFDB547B2" box="[463,514,966,991]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="302">rs-m</emphasis>
, areolet large, pentagonal, wider than high, 2 
<emphasis id="92C02C77FFAAFFDBADAC7FDDFB8047B2" box="[1023,1079,966,991]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="302">m-cu</emphasis>
weakly angulate with one wide bulla; hind wing nervellus reclivous; first tergite long and slender, completely fused with sternite, without carinae, spiracle at middle.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A00BF065FFAAFFDBAE94782AFCFB40B6" blockId="1.[151,1436,713,1243]" pageId="1" pageNumber="302">
<bibRefCitation id="C4258D94FFAAFFDBAE94782AFED84026" author="Townes, H. K." box="[199,367,1073,1099]" pageId="1" pageNumber="302" refId="ref9628" refString="Townes, H. K. (1970) The genera of Ichneumonidae, Part 2. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, No. 12, 1 - 537. [1969]" type="journal volume" year="1970">Townes (1970)</bibRefCitation>
places 
<taxonomicName id="67B48BE6FFAAFFDBAF92782AFDF54026" authorityName="Cushman" authorityYear="1922" box="[449,578,1073,1099]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Apophysius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="92C02C77FFAAFFDBAF92782AFDF54026" box="[449,578,1073,1099]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="302">Apophysius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in his subtribe 
<taxonomicName id="67B48BE6FFAAFFDBACBF782AFC304026" box="[748,903,1073,1099]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Bathytrichina">Bathytrichina</taxonomicName>
, together with 
<taxonomicName id="67B48BE6FFAAFFDBAA78782AFA894026" authority="Cameron" authorityName="Cameron" authorityYear="1902" box="[1067,1342,1073,1099]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Chrysocryptus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="92C02C77FFAAFFDBAA78782AFB794026" box="[1067,1230,1073,1099]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="302">Chrysocryptus</emphasis>
Cameron
</taxonomicName>
, a genus recently recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="D8A3B0F5FFAAFFDBAFF3784EFE484002" box="[416,511,1109,1135]" name="Vietnam" pageId="1" pageNumber="302">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="C4258D94FFAAFFDBAC5D784EFD634002" author="Pham, N. T. &amp; Broad, G. R. &amp; van Achterberg, C." box="[526,724,1109,1135]" pageId="1" pageNumber="302" pagination="60 - 66" refId="ref9477" refString="Pham, N. T., Broad, G. R. &amp; van Achterberg, C. (2019) A review of the genus Chrysocryptus Cameron (Ichneumonidae: Phygadeountinae), with description of a new species. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 67, 60 - 66." type="journal article" year="2019">
Pham 
<emphasis id="92C02C77FFAAFFDBAC04784DFD274002" box="[599,656,1109,1135]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="302">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
). Species of both genera have dense, long blond setae covering the head and mesosoma and slender first metasomal segments lacking carinae. 
<taxonomicName id="67B48BE6FFAAFFDBAA7B7862FB1E40FE" authorityName="Cushman" authorityYear="1922" box="[1064,1193,1145,1171]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Apophysius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="92C02C77FFAAFFDBAA7B7862FB1E40FE" box="[1064,1193,1145,1171]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="302">Apophysius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="67B48BE6FFAAFFDBAE877886FEC040DA" authorityName="Cameron" authorityYear="1902" box="[212,375,1181,1207]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Chrysocryptus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="92C02C77FFAAFFDBAE877886FEC040DA" box="[212,375,1181,1207]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="302">Chrysocryptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the indistinct notauli on the mesoscutum, the presence of two instead of three projections on the clypeus, and the two sets of apophyses on the propodeum.
</paragraph>
